Tepples: Quick question. In my own (naive) sound driver I've been writing, I assumed that I could just do a 0.4x0.4 -&gt; 0.4 multiply using a lookup table, since the NES only has 4 bit volumes anyway. (Other than triangle modulation by the DAC) ... Bit rotations are comparitively inexpensive, too, so even if I want something different (say 0.6x0.6 for MOD-like syntax) it shouldn't be that bad...<br /><br />Or am I missing something?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Thu Oct 23, 2008 4:37 pm</p><hr />
